threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a malicious IoT botnet variant, likely belonging to the Mirai family or a similar DDoS-focused strain. Key behaviors include network scanning via SSDP (M-SEARCH) in function sub_e898 to identify vulnerable UPnP devices, and the presence of exploit-related strings targeting Netis routers ('Self Rep Fucking NeTiS') in sub_dc58. The binary contains numerous functions (e.g., sub_df9c, sub_b590, sub_c46c) designed for packet crafting and network attacks. Relevant IOCs include the hardcoded C2 IP 151.243.109.76 and strings associated with SSDP discovery and device-specific exploits.
